  "prompt": "What are some good psychological thriller movies of 2015?",
  "response": "2015 was a great year for psychological thrillers! Here are some of the best, categorized for a bit more variety:\n\n**Highly Acclaimed & Popular:**\n\n*   **Room:** A mother and son held captive for years finally escape, but their ordeal is far from over as they adjust to the outside world. (Gripping, emotional, thought-provoking).\n*   **Sicario:** An FBI agent is enlisted by a government task force to bring down the leader of a powerful Mexican drug cartel, forcing her to question her own morality. (Intense, action-packed, morally complex).\n\n**Twisty & Mind-Bending:**\n\n*   **The Gift:** A young married couple's lives are thrown into disarray when a classmate from the husband's past begins leaving mysterious gifts. (Suspenseful, unsettling, secrets revealed).\n\n**Slow-Burn & Character-Driven:**\n\n*   **Mr. Holmes:** An aged and retired Sherlock Holmes grapples with an unsolved case from his past, challenging his legendary intellect and confronting his own mortality. (Subtle, character study, melancholic).\n*   **Regression:** A detective investigates a case of alleged satanic ritual abuse, uncovering repressed memories and dark secrets. (Atmospheric, unsettling, deals with controversial themes).\n\n**Smaller Gems & Underrated:**\n\n*   **Ex Machina:** A young programmer is selected to participate in a groundbreaking experiment in artificial intelligence by evaluating the human qualities of a highly advanced humanoid robot. (Smart, stylish, philosophical). *Although technically a sci-fi thriller, its psychological elements are very strong.*\n*   **Slow West:** A sixteen-year-old boy journeys across the American frontier in search of the woman he loves, accompanied by a mysterious traveler. (Beautifully shot, atmospheric, contains moments of brutal violence).\n\n**Things to consider when choosing:**\n\n*   **Your preferred pacing:** Some are fast-paced and action-oriented, while others are slow-burn and character-driven.\n*   **The type of psychological themes you enjoy:** Some explore morality, others repressed memories, and others the nature of reality.\n*   **Whether you prefer a twisty plot or a more character-focused narrative.**\n\nThis list offers a variety of styles within the psychological thriller genre. Enjoy your viewing!\n",
